sentences: Natasha Shanta Reid (born May 31, 1981), better known by her Korean name Yoon Mi-rae (Korean: 윤미래), is an American-born South Korean rapper and singer who is currently a member of Korean hip hop trio MFBTY.
Yoon was born on May 31, 1981, in Fort Hood, Texas to a South Korean mother and an African-American father.
Yoon was discovered in 1995 when she accompanied a friend to an audition for a new Korean hip hop group.
The group debuted in 1997, when Yoon was 16.
In 1999, she also formed hip hop and R&B duo "Tashannie" with rapper Lee Soo-a, stage name "Annie".
Uptown broke up in 2000 after several group members were arrested on drug charges.
Yoon debuted as a solo artist in 2001, under the moniker "T" which she shortened even more from "Tasha".
Her second album, Gemini and her third album, To My Love, were released the following year in 2002.
In 2006, she joined Jungle Entertainment, a label founded by her now-husband Tiger JK.
In 2012, Yoon became the face of the computer brand Hewlett-Packard in Korea, having signed a one-year contract to appear in their print media and radio advertisements.

She was also a judge on the third and fourth seasons of the television talent competition Superstar K. Yoon, Tiger JK and rapper Bizzy, formed the hip hop trio MFBTY (My Fans Better Than Yours) in 2013.
In September 2013, Yoon earned the #1 spot on Billboard's Korea K-Pop Hot 100 list with her song "Touch Love" from the South Korean drama Master's Sun.
In December 2014, Yoon released the single "Angel," which quickly became #1 on four Korean music charts.
In June 2007, she married Tiger JK in a private ceremony in a Buddhist Temple.
Yoon gave birth to their son Jordan Seo in March 2008.
In 2011, they appeared in a photoshoot with their son in Vogue Korea for the "Stop Child Abuse & Love Children" campaign.
They also filmed a public service announcement for the World Day for the Prevention of Child Abuse, performing at the 2011 Child Abuse Awareness Concert.
In 2012, South Korea's Ministry of Health and Welfare commended the couple for their efforts in promoting child abuse prevention.
In 2008, she volunteered for seven months at a multicultural youth camp.
